Remarks.

Porcellana sayana

is found often as a commensal of at least four hermit crabs (
Haig 1956
; 
Meireles & Mantelatto 2008
; 

Fransozo 
et al.
2011

; 
Brooks & Rittschof 2014
) and gastropods (
Telford & Daxboeck 1978
), or free living on sandy, muddy, and shell bottoms down to a depth of 
100 m
(
Werding 1982
; 
Veloso & Melo 1993
). One ovigerous female was found in association with the sponge crab, 

Dromia erythropus

(Edwards in Catesby, 1771) (CCDB 5299). Sequences accession numbers (GenBank): CCDB 3621—16S (
MF490163
), COI (
MF490063
) (

Mantelatto 
et al.
2018

).
